      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Baltimore Orioles baseball team has selected Richardson, Myers &amp; Donofrio Inc. in Baltimore to handle its account, which had been at Trahan, Burden &amp; Charles in Baltimore for four years. Billings were estimated at $2 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Baltimore Orioles baseball team has selected Richardson, Myers &amp; Donofrio Inc. in Baltimore to handle its account, which had been at Trahan, Burden &amp; Charles in Baltimore for four years. Billings were estimated at $2 million.</p>
        <p>Richardson, Myers was awarded the account after an informal, three-month review that included the incumbent. The change in agencies comes after an ownership group led by Peter G. Angelos bought the club in a Federal bankruptcy auction.  THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
